To deploy Cilium follow these steps:
1) annotate the K8s nodes with the following annotations:
    rack_id="<id>" This is the rack_id that you have allocated to your leaves. Nodes will peer with leaves with the same rack_id
2) Add the Cilium Helm Chart:
    helm repo add cilium https://helm.cilium.io/
4) (Optional) Edit the cilium-values.yaml file and set the k8sServiceHost and the k8sServicePort to the Control Plan Virtual IP:Port used by your K8s Cluster. 
    By default the VIP is  the cluster_subnet broadcast_address - 3 and the port is 8443.
5) Install Cilium: 
    helm install cilium cilium/cilium --version {{ heml_charts_versions['cilium/cilium'] }} --namespace kube-system -f cilium-values.yaml
6) Apply Cilium BGP Config Map
    kubectl apply -f cilium-bgp-config-map.yaml
7) Apply Cilium BGP Peering Policy
    kubectl apply -f cilium-bgp-config.yaml